\begin{abstract}
  The presence of discrete dividends complicates the derivation
  and form of pricing formulas even for vanilla options.
  Existing analytic, numerical, and theoretical approximations
  provide results of varying quality and performance.
  Here, we compare the analytic approach, developed and effective
  for European puts and calls, of Buryak and Guo
  with the formulas, designed in the context
  of barrier option pricing, of Dai and Chiu.
\end{abstract}

